entry.def: A timekeeper is a person or an instrument that records or checks the time.
If you say that someone is a good timekeeper, you mean that they usually arrive on time for things. If you say that they are a poor timekeeper, you mean that they are often late.

means.word_mean: 1. (sports) an official who keeps track of the time elapsed
2. a clerk who keeps track of the hours worked by employees
3. a measuring instrument or device for keeping time
